metadata.name: Broken Patterns Resolve #50
metadata.description: I derived this work from generative visual experiments I created way back in 2012. I was trying to make a Spirograph, also known as a Hypotrochoid if you're a mathy. I like the results of this broken code tangent more than the working version, and I revisited it from time to time. It's always special to pull a project out of the dustbin and make it dance again. Enjoy!

metadata.name: Flowingcles #59
metadata.description:
"Flowingcles" is a generative art piece that showcases a mesmerizing collection of  circles and abstract shapes. This unique collection invites art enthusiasts to embark on an inspiring visual journey.

Some pieces feature abstract shapes accompanied by a noise effect, reflecting restlessness and energy, while others present a more serene atmosphere with minimalized noise effects. These two approaches offer collectors the freedom to choose the one that resonates with them the most.

The "Flowingcles" collection consists of a total of 128 original pieces. Each artwork has been generated with a unique combination, ensuring individuality and distinctiveness. By incorporating these pieces into their collections, art enthusiasts can adorn their homes, offices, or galleries with a sense of unparalleled art experience and authenticity.

"Flowingcles" stands as a prominent example of modern art, showcasing dynamism, aesthetics, and originality. This collection pushes the boundaries of art and takes viewers on a captivating visual journey. Therefore, me invite art lovers to explore the "Flowingcles" collection and become a part of this visual spectacle:)

- S: Save a png file with the current resolution (2400*3400)

metadata.name: Chroma-Ville #31
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

The prefix 'Chroma' refers to the large color palette used in the Chroma series.

'Chroma-Ville' is the final creation in the 'Chroma' series. The arrangement of cubes creates an image reminiscent of a city-scape. Coupled with the carefully balanced colors, each output forms a bold, striking design.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: Zentangle #arizona #37
metadata.description:
Welcome to Arizona!
I have turned Arizona into a work of art in my own style
Play with lines, colors, plants, mountains and rocks
It was an interesting event for me in the style of the Arizona desert zoo
I hope you enjoy watching it too



This collection is the result of my playing with the lines I drew with the tablet.
This collection has 11 layers
The first layer contains the background
The second and third layer of ground and background lines
The fourth layer of mountains and rocks contains 21 images in zentangle style
The fifth layer of stones and rocks
The sixth layer of cacti
The next layers are rocks and deserts and flowers and plants
11th signature layer
